__SqlaTable__.sql:
select to_timestamp, value
from (
  select to_timestamp(time_bucket::text, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), (value::decimal / 10000) "value"
  from service_apdex
) t
where to_timestamp < (now() - interval '1 minute')
order by to_timestamp desc

select to_timestamp(t1.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI') , t1.value, t2.name
from endpoint_avg t1
inner join endpoint_traffic t2 on t1.entity_id = t2.id

--service response latency (percentile in ms)
select
  to_timestamp(dd.time_bucket, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 1), 3)::integer p50,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 2), 3)::integer p75,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 3), 3)::integer p90,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 4), 3)::integer p95,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 5), 3)::integer p99
from service_percentile ap
right join (
SELECT to_char(dd, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI') "time_bucket"
FROM generate_series(
  current_timestamp - '15 minutes'::interval,
  current_timestamp,
  '1 minute'::interval) dd
) dd on (ap.time_bucket = dd.time_bucket::bigint)

select to_timestamp(t1.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  t1.value "young_gc_count",
  t2.value "old_gc_count"
from instance_jvm_young_gc_count t1
inner join instance_jvm_old_gc_count t2 on t1.id = t2.id

select to_timestamp(t1.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  t1.value / 1048576 "heap",
  t2.value / 1048576 "heap_max",
  t3.value / 1048576 "noheap",
  t4.value / 1048576 "noheap_max"
from instance_jvm_memory_heap t1
inner join instance_jvm_memory_heap_max t2 on t1.id = t2.id
inner join instance_jvm_memory_noheap t3 on t2.id = t3.id
inner join instance_jvm_memory_noheap_max t4 on t3.id = t4.id

--endpoint response time (ms)
select
  to_timestamp(dd.time_bucket, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 1), 3)::integer p50,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 2), 3)::integer p75,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 3), 3)::integer p90,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 4), 3)::integer p95,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 5), 3)::integer p99,
  ap.entity_id,
  t1.name
from endpoint_percentile ap
inner join endpoint_traffic t1 on t1.id = ap.entity_id
right join (
SELECT to_char(dd, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI') "time_bucket"
FROM generate_series(
  current_timestamp - '15 minutes'::interval,
  current_timestamp,
  '1 minute'::interval) dd
) dd on (ap.time_bucket = dd.time_bucket::bigint)

select to_timestamp(t2.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), t1.name, t2.entity_id, t2.value
from endpoint_traffic t1
inner join endpoint_avg t2 on t1.id = t2.entity_id

select to_timestamp, value
from (
  select to_timestamp(time_bucket::text, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), value
  from service_cpm
) t
where to_timestamp < (now() - interval '1 minute')
order by to_timestamp desc

select to_timestamp(time_bucket::text, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), value
from service_resp_time
order by time_bucket desc

select to_timestamp(t1.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  t1.value "young_gc_time",
  t2.value "old_gc_time"
from instance_jvm_young_gc_time t1
inner join instance_jvm_old_gc_time t2 on t1.id = t2.id

--global response latency (percentile in ms)
select
  dd.id,
  to_timestamp(dd.id, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 1), 3)::integer p50,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 2), 3)::integer p75,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 3), 3)::integer p90,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 4), 3)::integer p95,
  substr(split_part(value, '|', 5), 3)::integer p99
from all_percentile ap
right join (
SELECT to_char(dd, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI') id
FROM generate_series(
  current_timestamp - '15 minutes'::interval,
  current_timestamp,
  '1 minute'::interval) dd
) dd on (ap.id = dd.id)

select to_timestamp(t2.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), t1.name, t2.entity_id, t2.percentage / 100 "value"
from endpoint_traffic t1
inner join endpoint_sla t2 on t1.id = t2.entity_id

select to_timestamp(t2.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'), t1.name, t2.entity_id, t2.value
from endpoint_traffic t1
inner join endpoint_cpm t2 on t1.id = t2.entity_id
